    "comment": "Rationale: Post-tetanic potentiation (PTP) at the TA-CA1 synapses was impaired in netrin-G1-KO.\nfEPSP potentiation by PDBu (a PKC activator; 0.4 μm) was reduced at TA-CA1 synapses in netrin-G1-KO.\nLTP induced by TBuS (an LTP-stimulation protocol) at the TA-CA1 synapses was attenuated in netrin-G1-KO.\nSynaptic potentiation following consecutive four TBuS trains was decreased in netrin-G1-KO.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods\nElectrophysiology.\nMice were deeply anesthetized with halothane (Takeda) and killed by decapitation.",
